A surprising passage through this gallery, open to the public, housing rooms from the Paris-Sorbonne and Sobronne Nouvelle universities and other Parisian universities and major schools. The headquarters of the National Institute of Art History and the National Heritage Institute are also present here. At first glance the entrance does not seem particularly inviting, with no shop in sight and a security guard at the entrance. However, the architecture of the place, the status of Eurydice (with a y that I never know where to place...) and the majestic dome in the background, a place of choice to enjoy the peaceful passages of Paris, far from the noise and the liveliness of the Vivienne gallery which is a few meters away!

caption: Les Passages couverts, Ouvert en 1826 According to the Paris tourist office: "Built in 1823, Galerie Colbert is a short walk from its main rival, Galerie Vivienne. This well-covered arcade belongs to the National Library and is unlike any other Parisian arcade. There are no shops here; there is a culturally oriented Institute (INHA) and a magnificent circular building covered by a glass dome, which is under the jurisdiction of the French Minister of Culture. The architecture is open to the public. The Art Nouveau brasserie, Le Grand Colbert, is listed as a historic building and is located at the entrance to the arcade.
Typically Parisian style gallery
Pleasant interior gallery in 18th century style. Free passage.

Galerie Colbert is located at 6 rue des Petits Champs, 4 rue Vivienne 75002 in the Quartier Vivienne, one of the 80 quartiers of Paris, within the borders of the 2e arrondissement, also known as de la Bourse ("Stock Exchange") of the capital of France, Paris. A luxurious passage. However, there are no shops inside and currently I.N.H.A. (Institut national d'histoire de l'art) and I.N.P. It is home to the (Institut national du patrimoine). Apart from its neighbor Galerie Vivienne, it is surrounded by prominent Parisian arcades such as Passage Bourg-l'Abbé and Passage du Grand Cerf.
